data.text:
WELCOME TO MORAY SPEYSIDE

Moray Speyside in the north of Scotland neighbours the Highlands to the west, the Cairngorms National Park to the south and Aberdeenshire to the east.

Moray Speyside is Scotland’s home to more than half of the country’s whisky distilleries including Macallan and Glenfiddich – Scotland’s first ever distillery visitor centre and to brands such as Walkers Shortbread, Baxters and Johnstons of Elgin.
